25/08/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Ivailo Kalfin announced on Wednesday (24 August) that the country is prepared to send medicine and medical equipment to treat Libyan children with HIV. Kalfin stresseds that the humanitarian aid would be part of a broader European initiative, and is not linked to the case of the five Bulgarian nurses sentenced to death in Libya on allegations -- which Bulgaria denies -- that they infected children with the virus. (bTV, Mediapool - 24/08/05)
